---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

export const prerender = true;
---

<Layout
  title="Terms and Conditions"
  description="Terms and conditions of Rij-Vrij Driving School, applicable to the lesson agreement. In force from 1 January 2025."
>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Terms and Conditions | Rij-Vrij Driving School</h1>

    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 p-4 bg-amber-50 border border-amber-100 rounded-xl">
      <strong>Note:</strong> These terms and conditions were drawn up in Dutch and the Dutch version is legally binding. The English translation below is provided for information purposes only.
    </p>

    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-10">These Terms and Conditions were established in consultation with all driving schools affiliated with Rij-Vrij Driving School, and take effect from 1 January 2025.</p>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Definitions</h2>
      <ul class="text-gray-600 space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
        <li><strong>Test:</strong> A test moment such as the driving ability assessment, theory exam, practical exams (AVB, AVD, B, B-H, AM2, BE, etc.), the Interim Driving Test (TTT) or the Code 95 test;</li>
        <li><strong>Practical training:</strong> A practical driving lesson;</li>
        <li><strong>Practical training package:</strong> The lesson agreement for a fixed number of lessons or for a fixed period;</li>
        <li><strong>Examination body:</strong> The Central Bureau of Driving Licences (CBR) / the Bureau for Further Driving Ability Assessment (BNOR) or another examination body;</li>
        <li><strong>In writing:</strong> In writing or electronically.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Article 1 – Applicability</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600">The Terms and Conditions apply to lesson agreements concluded between students and driving schools affiliated with Rij-Vrij Driving School.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Article 2 – The Agreement</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2">1. The lesson agreement specifies the type of training:</p>
      <ul class="text-gray-600 list-disc list-inside mb-4 space-y-1">
        <li>Theory training;</li>
        <li>Practical training;</li>
        <li>A practical training package;</li>
        <li>Other training.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-gray-600">2. The lesson agreement is recorded in writing. The student receives a copy of the lesson agreement.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Article 3 – Obligations of the driving school</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2">The driving school is obliged to ensure:</p>
      <ol class="text-gray-600 space-y-2 list-decimal list-inside">
        <li>That lessons are provided by instructors who meet the requirements of the Motor Vehicle Driving Instruction Act (WRM);</li>
        <li>That lessons are provided by the same instructor as much as possible;</li>
        <li>That the instructor regularly informs the student about their progress, also in relation to the exam requirements;</li>
        <li>That the application for a test is entered into the relevant examination body's application file within 2 weeks of payment;</li>
        <li>That the student can take the driving ability assessment in the lesson vehicle used during training on the scheduled date and time;</li>
        <li>That the agreed duration of a lesson is fully used for that lesson;</li>
        <li>That the driving school has taken out liability insurance with a minimum coverage of €2,500,000;</li>
        <li>That the student is informed which medical conditions may affect their right to drive a vehicle;</li>
        <li>That the student is informed that their residency status determines their right to obtain a driving licence;</li>
        <li>That the student is told they must report if their authority to drive a motor vehicle has been withdrawn.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Article 4 – Obligations of the student</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600">For the full Dutch text of the remaining articles, please refer to the Dutch version of these terms and conditions or contact us.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="mt-8 p-5 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl">
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">For the complete and legally binding terms and conditions (in Dutch), please <a href="/algemene-voorwaarden" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">click here</a> or contact us at <a href="mailto:info@rij-vrij.nl" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">info@rij-vrij.nl</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
